    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Acalypha burmanii are infusion, tincture, decoction, tea, and salve, each utilized for its medicinal properties. Infusion is used for its antioxidant and anti-inflammatory effects, made by steeping the leaves and flowers in hot water. Tincture, a concentrated liquid extract, is applied topically for skin conditions like eczema and dermatitis due to its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties. Decoction, a strong brew of roots and stems, is prepared to alleviate respiratory issues like bronchitis and asthma by its expectorant properties. Salve, a topical cream, is applied to wounds and skin irritations due to its antiseptic and antifungal properties.",
